 Experience is the mother of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42807.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>15. Humility is the beginning of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41159.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>16. Experience is the father of <em>wisdom</em> and memory the mother.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40854.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>17. It is <em>wisdom</em> sometimes to seem a fool.&nbsp;<a href='/s/43188.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>18. The past is for <em>wisdom</em>, the present for action, but for joy the future.&nbsp;<a href='/s/43879.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>19. <em>Wisdom</em> is to the mind what health is to the body.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42325.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>20. Experience is the mother [father] of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40858.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>21. <em>Wisdom</em> is more to be envied than riches.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42323.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>22. A flow of words is no proof of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40308.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>23. Books are the ever-burning lamps of accumulated <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40633.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>24. <em>Wisdom</em> is better than gold or silver.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42322.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>25. From hearing comes <em>wisdom</em>; from speaking repentance.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40943.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>26. That’s good <em>wisdom</em> which is wisdom in the end.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41899.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>27. An ounce of luck is better than a pound of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40491.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>28. To flee vice is the begnning of virtue, and to have got rid of folly is the beginning of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47339.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>29. Some of the best lessons we ever learn from our mistakes and failuresThe error of the past is the <em>wisdom</em> and success of the future.&nbsp;<a href='/s/43694.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div style="margin-bottom:3px;">30. The road of excess leads to the palace of <em>wisdom</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/46914.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div></div><!--all结束-->  <!--如果不是仅显示学生,或该页没有学生句子-->  <div id="student" style='display:none;'>  <div>1. Only with organization can the <em>wisdom</em> of th